        <h2>It All Started With a Disaster</h2>
        <p>
          It was the kind of moment you never forget. I had spent weeks setting up a custom **Windows Storage Spaces** array, convinced that this would be the most **reliable** and **secure** way to store my data. After all, it promised redundancy and fault tolerance, right?
        </p>

        <p>
          But then, disaster struck. A single disk failure led to a chain reaction, and before I knew it, **all of my data** was gone. My **important documents**, **family photos**, and **projects**—everything—was wiped out. The feeling of helplessness and devastation was palpable. It was more than just a hard drive failure; it felt like the loss of **memories** and hours of hard work that could never be recovered.
        </p>

        <h2>Searching for a Solution</h2>
        <p>
          I was determined to never face such a loss again. I began my search for **data protection** solutions that could give me peace of mind. That’s when I stumbled upon **Unraid**. I had heard whispers about it before, but it wasn’t until this catastrophe that I really understood its potential. 
        </p>

        <p>
          Unraid wasn’t just another RAID system that required matching hard drives or locked me into complicated configurations. It was a **flexible**, **scalable**, and **user-friendly** system that promised a new way to think about data storage. I knew instantly that this was the solution I had been looking for. 
        </p>

        <h2>Building My Homelab with Unraid</h2>
        <p>
          With Unraid in hand, I set out to build my **homelab** from the ground up. It started small—a few drives, an old PC I had lying around, and a few hours spent reading the documentation. But as I added more drives, set up **Docker containers**, and customized the system to my needs, my homelab started to grow.
        </p>

        <p>
          The beauty of Unraid lies in its flexibility. I could add any size drive, mix old and new hardware, and still have a system that would **never** lose my data. I also set up **parity disks**, ensuring that if a drive ever failed, my data would be safe. I didn’t have to worry about the **single point of failure** that caused my previous disaster.
        </p>

        <h2>From Data Loss to Empowerment</h2>
        <p>
          With Unraid, I no longer felt like a victim of technology—I felt like a **master** of it. My homelab became more than just a storage system. It became a playground for my passion: **automation**, **security**, and **efficiency**. I could experiment with **Docker**, set up **virtual machines**, automate tasks, and optimize my system with ease.
        </p>

        <p>
          What started as a recovery mission turned into a **new beginning**. I found myself delving deeper into self-hosting and **smart home automation**, building systems that **worked for me**, not the other way around. My tech skills grew as I tackled new challenges, from setting up **home security cameras** to learning about **networking** and even **cloud services**.
        </p>

        <h2>Why MardisTech Exists</h2>
        <p>
          I created **MardisTech** to share my experiences and the knowledge I gained from my **data disaster** to **Unraid success**. It’s not just about homelabs or tech setups—it’s about **taking control** of your own digital world. Whether you're just starting or have years of experience, I want to help others avoid the mistakes I made and empower them to build **reliable, self-sustaining systems**.
        </p>

        <p>
          On this blog, I’ll share:
